ZCZC GE49
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE CENTRED NORWEGIAN
SEA 994 AND THIS IS LIKELY TO SLWY FILL AND DRIFT AWAY NEWARDS. A RIDGE OF
HIGH PRESSURE WILL THEN MOV EWARDS ACROSS THE UK BY WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON.
OVERNIGHT PRESSURE WILL CONTINUE TO RISE ACROSS ALL WATERS OF CULLERCOATS
AND BY MIDDAY WEDNESDAY A HIGH MAY BE CENTRED VIKING 1022. OVERNIGHT THIS
AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE IS MOST LIKELY TO MOV AWAY E ALLOWING A BROAD TROUGH
TO EXTEND S AND E ACROSS NERN WATERS OF CULLERCOATS BY THURSDAY MORNING.
THIS WILL THEN PROBABLY BE FOLLOWED BY A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE BY EVENING
WHICH MAY EXTEND FM SEA AREA THAMES THROUGH DOGGER AND ACROSS EERN WATERS
OF FAIR ISLE. THE GREATEST RISK OF GALES WILL PROBABLY BE ACROSS FAIR ISLE
